And now that I have a had a second to digest the events of Sunday, I can post.🤣
Let me start by saying that I LOVE being a fan of this team. I love the team and I love the community that is BILLS MAFIA. 
And the loss didn’t hurt as bad as last year. I don’t have reoccurring dreams of 13 seconds of heartache and disbelief. 
We didn’t show up to win. It wasn’t our year. And even if we squeaked out a win, we weren’t Super Bowl material unless we did a full switcheroo of some kind. 

Here is what I do know….our team has heart and the pieces are there. Some need to change and our game plan must be better. But we have it in us to get to the AFC championship game with confidence and then…beyond. 
I will enjoy this coming weekend without a care. It’s gonna be some excellent football. And I will miss wearing my @waterbuffaloclub716 hat but will be fired up and ready for next season! Love you @buffalobills and @buffalofambase #billsmafia

***ANNNNDDDD LAKE LAG IS FULL!

Melanoma Awareness Month!  I have had 4 melanoma. The deadliest form of skin cancer. I hesitated posting a picture of me at the beach but I think it’s important for people to think of sun safety and skin cancer awareness, realistically. When I go out in the sun, I don’t stay out for long. I always completely and, according to my family, annoyingly slather myself with sunscreen. But I still love the sun. I just know my limits. I also know to check my skin! Skin cancer shows it’s face to you!!! So, before you unveil your awesome new swimsuit, take a moment in your birthday suit and look for anything NEW, DIFFERENT, DARKER, or THAT CATCHES YOUR EYE! And MAKE YOUR APPOINTMENT WITH A DERMATOLOGIST FOR YOUR SKIN CHECK! It’s all about catching it early, like I did!!! Let’s enjoy the spring and summer together. See you in the water. 

#getnaked #melanoma #melanomaawareness #melanomamonday

When I was super young, maybe 10 years old, I wanted to go to USC because I knew I wanted to work in TV. But then, when I was 11, I went to a swim meet at Stanford University. I heard George Haines do his spoof on the call of a horse race. “Toothpaste is getting squeezed on the inside!” 
After that one visit, my dream changed. I knew I wanted to go to Stanford. And then the stars aligned when Richard Quick became the head coach. 

For my entire life, I loved and dreamed of swimming in the PAC-10…now 12. 

I am so sad that the world of college sports is changing so dramatically. I am not mad, I am just sad. I will forever hold onto my wonderful memories of being a proud PAC-10 athlete. Always staying up for our ridiculously late games while living in NYC. 

Please take care of these athletes. Please continue to understand that Olympic athletes need the NCAA model to fulfill their dreams. My NCAA experience included the greatest moment in my swimming career…our Championship in 1992 as a team! 

Just wanted to share♥️♥️♥️

When you meet your heroes♥️🥰😭💃 
This was magical. I quit swimming for a second during the summer of my 11th year. Lucky for me, my LA born dad was hell-bent on taking us to the ‘84 games. I watched those athletes in awe and I cheered carrying my little American flag with me wherever I went. I was obsessed with Mary Lou. That vault…the pressure…and of course, her smile and vibrancy! Well, yesterday, I got to sit next to her and interview her for our @teamusa meetings. Crazy how life works! I felt like I was 11 again. 

Oh yeah, after those ‘84 Games, I decided to go back to the pool and that is how my Olympic dream began♥️ 🇺🇸 #gousa

Today is my birthday. Proud 51! Started the day with a bit of a jog through one of the most gorgeous areas in UT. Erik rode the bike next to me. The autumn scene was so breathtaking that we kept saying…”this is such an amazing day! I feel so lucky!”

And I know that sounds strange as today is Friday the 13th but 51 years ago, at 7:59pm I was born on Friday the 13th! So, for me, it’s a good day! 

And then, Skye wrote me the sweetest birthday card. And, of course, I was bawling as I read it out loud.

It’s been an amazing birthday filled with so many messages of love, which filled my gratitude cup. Thank you all. Sending the love back out to the world♥️♥️♥️ Happy Birthday to all the other Oct 13th’ers out there!
#gobills
